Verity Lambert - Drama Queen - ( Doctor Who ) 04-05-2008

DOCUMENTARY: Verity Lambert: Drama Queen 
On: BBC 4 
Date: Saturday 5th April 2008 
Time: 21:50 to 22:50 

Tribute to TV producer Verity Lambert, who died in November 2007. From the original 

Doctor Who to Jonathan Creek, her 43-year career spanned the highs and lows of 

pioneering TV drama, and included The Naked Civil Servant, Edward and Mrs Simpson, 

Minder, May To December and Eldorado. Friends and colleagues including John Hurt, 

Alan Davies, Lynda La Plante and David Renwick, pay their respects to the woman who 

helped transform the face of popular television.
